AU  - Conrad, Douglas A.
AU  - Morrisey, Michael A.
Y1  - 1985/04/01
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1985.4278245
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1985.4278245
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 337
EP  - 343
VL  - 10
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Smith and Mick identify four basic problems with the theory the present writers developed to explain organizational responses (in this case the behavior of hospitals) to regulation. They challenge the basic assumption regarding autonomy, disagree with the implied cause and effect relations between organizational response and regulation, criticize the omission of goals, and claim that the theory has only limited generality. In so doing they state that their primary concern is with ?improving our understanding of the limitations and benefits of the theory.? Each of the four topics they raise for consideration will receive comment.
AB  - Smith and Mick identify four basic problems with the theory the present writers developed to explain organizational responses (in this case the behavior of hospitals) to regulation. They challenge the basic assumption regarding autonomy, disagree with the implied cause and effect relations between organizational response and regulation, criticize the omission of goals, and claim that the theory has only limited generality. In so doing they state that their primary concern is with ?improving our understanding of the limitations and benefits of the theory.? Each of the four topics they raise for consideration will receive comment.
